	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=9&mid=99967039772304>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99967039772304>RE: Weapons for shamans</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99967039772304#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Sep 5th 2:13 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=91078><span id=Sage>Shabura</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>104 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I tend to disagree with the suggestion of 2hB weapons for shaman.&nbsp;&nbsp;Shaman are not intended to use melee damage as a primary effect.  Now, I am not saying that shaman should not consider moving to melee under some conditions...I myself often do, when I am appropriately equipped.  My objection to the use of a 2hB is in the oppurtunity cost..that is to say, what one loses by doing so.<br><br>As you approach the early part of late game (50-56ish), you will discover that there are 2 very important stats.  First, AC.  AC is essential to a shaman, especially until you reach the level at which raids primarily focus on a single tank maintaining aggro.  Until that point, shaman will periodically be summoned, and the mobs responsible are not so powerful as to negate the use of AC.  Second, and likely more telling, are resists.  This is the era of dragon raids for a character.  AoE damage, Fear, and their ilk are MUCH more damaging than a smaller (or total lack) of shaman melee damage.  By not wielding a 1H weapon, shaman sacrifice the capacity to carry a beneficial shield.<br><br>Shield are very good for shaman in this game.  Some, like the CGS, Strathbone Shell Shield, and Crystal Chitin Shield, offering varying degrees of AC protection along with healthy amounts of Wisdom (valuable for the low-wis races that shaman can come from...).  At later levels, many shaman players will remark upon the Sarnak Battle Shield as an expensive, but well-deserved choice.<br><br>While I feel that there is nothign wrong in maintaining skills, it is important to note that these shields, and the total superiority of the Spear of Fate to other shaman items, makes 2hB a poor choice for long-term development.<br><br>Shabura</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
